    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite all 13 credibility factors showing achieved levels below required levels and 6 factors not assessed, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the Monte Carlo UQ bounds remain below the clinical hemolysis threshold under conservative assumptions. The decision reflects regulatory time pressure and is conditional on remediation of identified gaps prior to submission. Note: the ContextOfUse contains no structured applicability constraint or operating envelope specification; the valid operating range of the model is described only in prose, leaving the boundary of legitimate model use formally unspecified.",
